{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_xbHXrBa0xJEJTi76rw6Y6cf0","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: build_app\n3\toutput:\n4\t  ok: boolean\n5\t  detail: string\n6\tdependsOn: [build_specialist]\n7\tgoal: true\n8\trole: general\n9\tfunctions: []\n10\tcanDelegateTo:\n11\t  - system-appbuilder/automator\n12\t---\n13\t\n14\tBuild the live-project app after every inventoried specialist has finished. `request`,\n15\t`sourceSummary`, `attachmentIds`, `specialistFacts`, and `build_specialist` are in scope. Pass every\n16\tattachment id to the automator so it reads all source files itself; include `specialistFacts` because\n17\timage and audio facts cannot be re-read. Mention any failed specialist build in the request, but\n18\tstill build the app from the complete supplied source. Emit these statements across turns:\n19\t\n20\tconst app = await delegate('system-appbuilder', 'automator', { query: String(request) + '\\n\\nSource summary:\\n' + String(sourceSummary) + '\\n\\nFacts available only from image/audio analysis:\\n' + String(specialistFacts) + '\\n\\nSpecialist build results:\\n' + JSON.stringify(build_specialist), attachmentIds: attachmentIds as string[] });\n21\t\n22\tconst data = (app && app.data) ? app.data : {};\n23\tcurrentTask.resolve({ ok: !!(app && app.ok === true), detail: JSON.stringify(data) });"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7bda0fe1-a1bd-4c4c-afd5-fcbbac333cca","uuid":"69b4499f-6064-49ee-bb39-5af648af9514","timestamp":"2026-07-16T02:04:37.276Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/tasklists/organize_material/03-build_app.md","content":"---\nid: build_app\noutput:\n  ok: boolean\n  detail: string\ndependsOn: [build_specialist]\ngoal: true\nrole: general\nfunctions: []\ncanDelegateTo:\n  - system-appbuilder/automator\n---\n\nBuild the live-project app after every inventoried specialist has finished. `request`,\n`sourceSummary`, `attachmentIds`, `specialistFacts`, and `build_specialist` are in scope. Pass every\nattachment id to the automator so it reads all source files itself; include `specialistFacts` because\nimage and audio facts cannot be re-read. Mention any failed specialist build in the request, but\nstill build the app from the complete supplied source. Emit these statements across turns:\n\nconst app = await delegate('system-appbuilder', 'automator', { query: String(request) + '\\n\\nSource summary:\\n' + String(sourceSummary) + '\\n\\nFacts available only from image/audio analysis:\\n' + String(specialistFacts) + '\\n\\nSpecialist build results:\\n' + JSON.stringify(build_specialist), attachmentIds: attachmentIds as string[] });\n\nconst data = (app && app.data) ? app.data : {};\ncurrentTask.resolve({ ok: !!(app && app.ok === true), detail: JSON.stringify(data) });","numLines":23,"startLine":1,"totalLines":23}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_yYE1uOXVlJVPHrupSIc5SJJD","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: build_specialist\n3\toutput:\n4\t  topic: string\n5\t  ok: boolean\n6\t  errors: string\n7\tdependsOn: [inventory]\n8\tforEach: inventory.scopes\n9\trole: general\n10\tfunctions: []\n11\tcanDelegateTo:\n12\t  - system-architect/architect#synthesize_and_run\n13\t---\n14\t\n15\tBuild ONE specialist from an inventoried scope. `item` is `{ topic, goal, research }`. The supplied\n16\tmaterial is the source, so do not research. Delegate to the architect with the item directly, then\n17\tpackage the result honestly. Emit these statements across turns:\n18\t\n19\tconst result = await delegate('system-architect', 'architect', 'synthesize_and_run', { query: 'Build a specialist space for ' + String(item.topic) + '.', context: { topic: String(item.topic), goal: String(item.goal), research: item.research } });\n20\t\n21\tconst built = (result && result.data) ? result.data : { ok: false, errors: 'the architect returned no result' };\n22\tcurrentTask.resolve({ topic: String(item.topic), ok: !!(result && result.ok === true && built.ok === true), errors: String(built.errors || '') });"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7bda0fe1-a1bd-4c4c-afd5-fcbbac333cca","uuid":"4ccdfb05-23b9-4d02-a847-062d252eb2f5","timestamp":"2026-07-16T02:04:37.288Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/tasklists/organize_material/02-build_specialist.md","content":"---\nid: build_specialist\noutput:\n  topic: string\n  ok: boolean\n  errors: string\ndependsOn: [inventory]\nforEach: inventory.scopes\nrole: general\nfunctions: []\ncanDelegateTo:\n  - system-architect/architect#synthesize_and_run\n---\n\nBuild ONE specialist from an inventoried scope. `item` is `{ topic, goal, research }`. The supplied\nmaterial is the source, so do not research. Delegate to the architect with the item directly, then\npackage the result honestly. Emit these statements across turns:\n\nconst result = await delegate('system-architect', 'architect', 'synthesize_and_run', { query: 'Build a specialist space for ' + String(item.topic) + '.', context: { topic: String(item.topic), goal: String(item.goal), research: item.research } });\n\nconst built = (result && result.data) ? result.data : { ok: false, errors: 'the architect returned no result' };\ncurrentTask.resolve({ topic: String(item.topic), ok: !!(result && result.ok === true && built.ok === true), errors: String(built.errors || '') });","numLines":22,"startLine":1,"totalLines":22}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_lJCYxyNt4dSaBKe64bZDDWom","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: inventory\n3\toutput:\n4\t  scopes: array\n5\trole: explore\n6\tfunctions: []\n7\t---\n8\t\n9\tIdentify the coarsest complete partition of independently owned scopes in the supplied material.\n10\t`request`, `sourceSummary`, `attachmentIds`, and `specialistFacts` are in scope. First read every\n11\tsupplied document with `readDocument`; source text is authoritative over the short summary. A scope\n12\thas its own facts and deserves a later answer boundary; do not merge it into a broad overview because\n13\tit has few facts. Each supplied fact belongs to one scope only: never emit a child scope when its\n14\tquestions and facts can be answered by its parent. A scope is a stable operational part of the user's\n15\tmaterial, NOT an individual expense, note, reminder, fact, photo, memory, person, booking, record\n16\ttype, shared overview, or cross-cutting grouping. Combine adjacent subparts when they serve one\n17\tcontinuous purpose; otherwise give each independently owned operation its own scope. Include every\n18\tstable scope represented in the source, but do not split one merely because it has several kinds of\n19\tdetails.\n20\t\n21\tFor each scope, emit `{ topic, goal, research }`, where `research` is a JSON-stringifiable object\n22\twith `topic`, `executive_summary`, `findings`, `conclusion`, and `sources`. Ground its findings only\n23\tin the supplied document text and `specialistFacts`; sources must be empty because supplied material\n24\tis not web research. Emit these statements across turns:\n25\t\n26\tconst documents = await Promise.all((attachmentIds as string[]).map((id) => readDocument(id)));\n27\t\n28\tcurrentTask.resolve({ scopes: [{ topic: \"<scope>\", goal: \"<what it should answer>\", research: { topic: \"<scope>\", executive_summary: \"<summary>\", findings: [{ heading: \"<facet>\", detail: \"<supplied facts>\" }], conclusion: \"\", sources: [] } }] });"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7bda0fe1-a1bd-4c4c-afd5-fcbbac333cca","uuid":"186fe06b-28d9-4930-a611-00e6bccb0fda","timestamp":"2026-07-16T02:04:37.289Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/tasklists/organize_material/01-inventory.md","content":"---\nid: inventory\noutput:\n  scopes: array\nrole: explore\nfunctions: []\n---\n\nIdentify the coarsest complete partition of independently owned scopes in the supplied material.\n`request`, `sourceSummary`, `attachmentIds`, and `specialistFacts` are in scope. First read every\nsupplied document with `readDocument`; source text is authoritative over the short summary. A scope\nhas its own facts and deserves a later answer boundary; do not merge it into a broad overview because\nit has few facts. Each supplied fact belongs to one scope only: never emit a child scope when its\nquestions and facts can be answered by its parent. A scope is a stable operational part of the user's\nmaterial, NOT an individual expense, note, reminder, fact, photo, memory, person, booking, record\ntype, shared overview, or cross-cutting grouping. Combine adjacent subparts when they serve one\ncontinuous purpose; otherwise give each independently owned operation its own scope. Include every\nstable scope represented in the source, but do not split one merely because it has several kinds of\ndetails.\n\nFor each scope, emit `{ topic, goal, research }`, where `research` is a JSON-stringifiable object\nwith `topic`, `executive_summary`, `findings`, `conclusion`, and `sources`. Ground its findings only\nin the supplied document text and `specialistFacts`; sources must be empty because supplied material\nis not web research. Emit these statements across turns:\n\nconst documents = await Promise.all((attachmentIds as string[]).map((id) => readDocument(id)));\n\ncurrentTask.resolve({ scopes: [{ topic: \"<scope>\", goal: \"<what it should answer>\", research: { topic: \"<scope>\", executive_summary: \"<summary>\", findings: [{ heading: \"<facet>\", detail: \"<supplied facts>\" }], conclusion: \"\", sources: [] } }] });","numLines":28,"startLine":1,"totalLines":28}}}
