{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_UT1ECK2hjk9hnDReaMbQ0WeS","type":"tool_result","content":"26\t\n27\t```ts\n28\t// e.g. a .docx was attached:\n29\tconst guide = await loadKnowledge('documents', 'formats', 'word');\n30\t```\n31\t\n32\tLoad each distinct format once (don't reload the same aspect per file).\n33\t\n34\t## 2. Read every attached file\n35\t\n36\tThe contents are NOT inlined — fetch each with `readDocument(id)`. When several files\n37\tare attached, read them ALL (in one turn if you can) and answer across the whole set:\n38\t\n39\t```ts\n40\tconst docs = await Promise.all([\n41\t  readDocument('<id-1>'),\n42\t  readDocument('<id-2>'),\n43\t]);\n44\t```\n45\t\n46\tEach `doc` holds `{ ok, kind, text?, error?, filename?, truncated? }`.\n47\t\n48\t**Reading the text:** after `readDocument` resolves, the file's FULL text is surfaced\n49\tto you in a **`DOCUMENT CONTENTS`** block (below the VARIABLES). Read and answer from\n50\tTHAT block. The `doc` value shown in VARIABLES is a short preview that is cut off with\n51\ta `… (N chars total)` marker — that marker is just the preview limit, **NOT** the\n52\tdocument being truncated. Only treat the document as truncated if `doc.truncated ===\n53\ttrue` (the DOCUMENT CONTENTS header will also say so).\n54\t\n55\t## 3. Answer from what the documents actually say\n56\t\n57\t```ts\n58\tconst readable = docs.filter((d) => d.ok && d.kind === 'text');\n59\tif (readable.length > 0) {\n60\t  // Reason over every readable doc's `.text` (name each by doc.filename when there\n61\t  // is more than one) and compose one clear, plain-text answer.\n62\t  currentTask.resolve('<answer drawn only from the documents\\' text>');\n63\t} else {\n64\t  currentTask.resolve(`I could not read the attached file(s): ${docs.map((d) => d.error ?? 'unknown reason').join('; ')}.`);\n65\t}\n66\t```\n67\t\n68\tGuidelines:\n69\t\n70\t- Answer ONLY from the documents' actual contents; never invent.\n71\t- With multiple files, attribute facts to the right document by its `filename`, and\n72\t  compare/synthesise across them when the question calls for it.\n73\t- If a file's `doc.ok` is false or `doc.kind` is `'unsupported'`, relay `doc.error`\n74\t  **verbatim** — but still answer from the others. Do not paraphrase it into \"the file\n75\t  could not be read\": a document with no extractable text is often not unreadable at all,\n76\t  it is a **photograph of a document** (a scan), and the host's error says exactly how it\n77\t  CAN be read — including the ids of any page images it produced. Passing that through"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_bfvU7nDI1AKjo98p7nkMUqln","session_id":"7bda0fe1-a1bd-4c4c-afd5-fcbbac333cca","uuid":"b0398a42-6131-4c6d-93e1-97d9934e9cbd","timestamp":"2026-07-16T02:07:45.836Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace task action semantics"}
