{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_H7JetGEcpDMTU7bkWiXuoDM4","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# LMThing — Core Runtime Developer Guide (`sdk/org`)\n2\t\n3\tThe agent runtime and everything built directly on it: `@lmthing/core` (QuickJS WASM sandbox, streaming\n4\tstatement pipeline, yield protocol, spaces/forks/delegates/tasklists, typecheck, budgets), `@lmthing/cli`\n5\t(the `lmthing` binary + pod server), the shared libs, and the unified web SPA (`apps/web`).\n6\t\n7\tThe model does not call tools — **the model writes TypeScript**, one statement at a time, and the host\n8\tevaluates each statement as it streams in. A value-yielding call suspends the VM, aborts the stream, is\n9\tresolved host-side, and the results come back as a `VARIABLES` block on the next turn.\n10\t\n11\t## Source of truth — read this first\n12\t\n13\t> **[`org/docs/`](../../org/docs/README.md) (published at lmthing.org) is the single source of truth for\n14\t> this codebase.** Every factual sentence there carries a citation to the code that makes it true — a\n15\t> symbol anchor (`path#Symbol`) by preference, a line anchor (`path:Lstart-Lend`) where a symbol isn't\n16\t> appropriate. `pnpm docs:check` resolves them all as a hard CI gate. When this file disagrees with\n17\t> `org/docs`, `org/docs` wins. When `org/docs` disagrees with the **code**, the code wins and `org/docs`\n18\t> is fixed.\n19\t>\n20\t> **A change to code is not done until the matching `org/docs` page is updated in the same change.**\n21\t> The rule, the grounding convention, and the \"which doc moves with my change?\" table →\n22\t> [`org/docs/SYNC.md`](../../org/docs/SYNC.md).\n23\t\n24\tThis file is an **orientation index**: what lives here, how to run it, and where the real answer is.\n25\tKnowledge does not live here.\n26\t\n27\t## Workspace\n28\t\n29\t```bash\n30\tcd sdk/org\n31\tpnpm install                       # from lockfile\n32\tpnpm build                         # turbo run build → dist/\n33\tpnpm typecheck                     # tsc --noEmit across all packages (strict)\n34\tpnpm test                          # vitest run (co-located tests) — run from sdk/org, NOT the repo root\n35\tpnpm test libs/core/src/tasklist   # one directory / substring filter"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_bfvU7nDI1AKjo98p7nkMUqln","session_id":"7bda0fe1-a1bd-4c4c-afd5-fcbbac333cca","uuid":"e7dbfde2-0a02-45f7-b92a-c618de8be76e","timestamp":"2026-07-16T02:09:39.559Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace task action semantics"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_JlPLfoiRQFCFapbXqlAMVb0F","type":"tool_result","content":"378\t});\n379\t\n380\t// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n381\t// Bug fixes — observed through a mock-driven Session\n382\t// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n383\t\n384\tdescribe('mock-driven Session — bug fixes', () => {\n385\t  it('process.exit() ends the run cleanly instead of retrying the same code', async () => {\n386\t    const m = createMockStreamFn(() => 'process.exit(1);'); // every turn, if it retried\n387\t    const r = await runMockSession({ streamFn: m, message: 'go' });\n388\t    expect(r.error).toBeUndefined();\n389\t    expect(llmRequests(r.trace, 'session').length).toBe(1); // NOT retried 3×\n390\t  });\n391\t\n392\t  it('a `let` declared without an initializer is visible to a later statement', async () => {\n393\t    // Repro of variable-scoping-let-across-statements: declare in one statement,\n394\t    // reference in the next. Without propagation this throws ReferenceError.\n395\t    const m = createMockStreamFn((_o, { callIndex }) =>\n396\t      callIndex === 0 ? `let parsed;\\ndisplay(\"parsed is \" + parsed);` : '',\n397\t    );\n398\t    const r = await runMockSession({ streamFn: m, message: 'go' });\n399\t    expect(r.trace.some((e) => e.type === 'eval_error')).toBe(false);\n400\t    expect(r.displays).toContain('parsed is undefined');\n401\t  });\n402\t\n403\t  it('a default (non-scratch) agent cannot call execShell — it is off the model DTS (only fs:scratch earns it)', async () => {\n404\t    // The generic shell was removed from every agent's surface except the engineer's scratch\n405\t    // sandbox. A default agent calling execShell fails typecheck (Cannot find name 'execShell'),\n406\t    // so the statement never runs. (execShell's own {ok,stdout,stderr,exitCode} shape + the\n407\t    // scratch round-trip are unit-tested in spaces/system-functions.test.ts.)\n408\t    const m = createMockStreamFn((_o, { callIndex }) =>\n409\t      callIndex === 0 ? `const r = execShell(\"exit 5\");\\ndisplay(\"exit=\" + r.exitCode);` : '',\n410\t    );\n411\t    const r = await runMockSession({ streamFn: m, message: 'go' });\n412\t    expect(r.trace.some((e) => e.type === 'typecheck_error')).toBe(true);\n413\t    expect(r.displays).not.toContain('exit=5');\n414\t  });\n415\t\n416\t  it('a variable bound before a mid-turn error survives into the retry', async () => {\n417\t    // Repro of the architect death-spiral: turn 1 binds `phase1` (success → globalThis),\n418\t    // then a later statement in the SAME turn errors. The retry references `phase1`.\n419\t    // Before the fix, the error rollback wiped `phase1` from the typecheck context\n420\t    // (while it still lived in the VM), so the retry failed with \"Cannot find name\n421\t    // 'phase1'\" and burned all 3 attempts. The retry must now typecheck and run.\n422\t    let attempt = 0;"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_bfvU7nDI1AKjo98p7nkMUqln","session_id":"7bda0fe1-a1bd-4c4c-afd5-fcbbac333cca","uuid":"a5fc595e-10f6-418d-a5ba-8da397202d49","timestamp":"2026-07-16T02:09:39.561Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace task action semantics"}
