{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_eFLDGbhEkyelTlM1tLS5H4mp","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: investigate\n3\toutput:\n4\t  question: string\n5\t  findings: string\n6\t  sources: array\n7\t  confidence: string\n8\t  gaps: string\n9\tdependsOn: [plan]\n10\tforEach: plan.questions\n11\toptional: false\n12\trole: explore\n13\tfunctions:\n14\t  - webSearch\n15\t  - webFetch\n16\tprelude: |\n17\t  const question = String(item);\n18\t  const search = question ? await webSearch(question, { depth: \"advanced\", maxResults: 6 }) : { ok: false, answer: \"\", results: [] };\n19\t  const top = (search.results ?? []).slice(0, 3);\n20\t  const page1 = top[0] ? await webFetch(top[0].url, { format: \"markdown\" }) : { ok: false, content: \"\" };\n21\t  const page2 = top[1] ? await webFetch(top[1].url, { format: \"markdown\" }) : { ok: false, content: \"\" };\n22\t  const page3 = top[2] ? await webFetch(top[2].url, { format: \"markdown\" }) : { ok: false, content: \"\" };\n23\t---\n24\t\n25\tYou investigate ONE research question in isolation. The gathering ALREADY ran (see the prelude\n26\tresults in scope): `question` is your question, `search` its web search, `top` the top 3 results,\n27\tand `page1`/`page2`/`page3` their fetched pages. Do NOT search or fetch again — your budget of one\n28\tsearch and three fetches is spent. Your parent sees only the object you resolve — so synthesize,\n29\tdo not dump.\n30\t\n31\tWrite `findings`: a 5-8 sentence synthesis grounded in `search.answer` and the three fetched\n32\tpages, with concrete facts, figures, dates, and names — base it ONLY on what you actually read,\n33\tnever fabricate. Build `sources` as `[{ title, url }]` from `top`.\n34\t\n35\tThen assess your own evidence honestly:\n36\t- `confidence`: `\"high\"` if multiple fetched pages corroborate the same facts, `\"medium\"` if only\n37\t  one page or the search answer supported the findings, `\"low\"` if pages failed to fetch or were\n38\t  thin/off-topic.\n39\t- `gaps`: one sentence on what remains unknown, contested, or under-sourced for this question\n40\t  (empty string `\"\"` only if you are genuinely confident nothing is missing).\n41\t\n42\tIf the search was unavailable or returned nothing, use `findings = \"No sources were available for\n43\tthis question.\"`, `sources = []`, `confidence = \"low\"`, `gaps = \"No live sources were available.\"`.\n44\tThen emit ONE statement:\n45\t\n46\tcurrentTask.resolve({ question, findings, sources, confidence, gaps });\n47\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7bda0fe1-a1bd-4c4c-afd5-fcbbac333cca","uuid":"571a0342-d56c-471f-b44c-f303ee6fb85e","timestamp":"2026-07-16T02:10:36.223Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-research/tasklists/deep_research/03-investigate.md","content":"---\nid: investigate\noutput:\n  question: string\n  findings: string\n  sources: array\n  confidence: string\n  gaps: string\ndependsOn: [plan]\nforEach: plan.questions\noptional: false\nrole: explore\nfunctions:\n  - webSearch\n  - webFetch\nprelude: |\n  const question = String(item);\n  const search = question ? await webSearch(question, { depth: \"advanced\", maxResults: 6 }) : { ok: false, answer: \"\", results: [] };\n  const top = (search.results ?? []).slice(0, 3);\n  const page1 = top[0] ? await webFetch(top[0].url, { format: \"markdown\" }) : { ok: false, content: \"\" };\n  const page2 = top[1] ? await webFetch(top[1].url, { format: \"markdown\" }) : { ok: false, content: \"\" };\n  const page3 = top[2] ? await webFetch(top[2].url, { format: \"markdown\" }) : { ok: false, content: \"\" };\n---\n\nYou investigate ONE research question in isolation. The gathering ALREADY ran (see the prelude\nresults in scope): `question` is your question, `search` its web search, `top` the top 3 results,\nand `page1`/`page2`/`page3` their fetched pages. Do NOT search or fetch again — your budget of one\nsearch and three fetches is spent. Your parent sees only the object you resolve — so synthesize,\ndo not dump.\n\nWrite `findings`: a 5-8 sentence synthesis grounded in `search.answer` and the three fetched\npages, with concrete facts, figures, dates, and names — base it ONLY on what you actually read,\nnever fabricate. Build `sources` as `[{ title, url }]` from `top`.\n\nThen assess your own evidence honestly:\n- `confidence`: `\"high\"` if multiple fetched pages corroborate the same facts, `\"medium\"` if only\n  one page or the search answer supported the findings, `\"low\"` if pages failed to fetch or were\n  thin/off-topic.\n- `gaps`: one sentence on what remains unknown, contested, or under-sourced for this question\n  (empty string `\"\"` only if you are genuinely confident nothing is missing).\n\nIf the search was unavailable or returned nothing, use `findings = \"No sources were available for\nthis question.\"`, `sources = []`, `confidence = \"low\"`, `gaps = \"No live sources were available.\"`.\nThen emit ONE statement:\n\ncurrentTask.resolve({ question, findings, sources, confidence, gaps });\n","numLines":47,"startLine":1,"totalLines":47}}}
